      "α)) where\n  root : α\n  children : List (ListTree α)\n```\n\nThis is a recursive structure. The root is `α`, and the children are `List (ListTree α)`. So each child is a `ListTree α`.\n\nThe membership operation `∈` for `ListTree` would check if the value is the root, or if it's in one of the children.\n\nBut in our case, `valid` has `scopes : ListTree (ThreadId)`. So the root is a `ThreadId`, and the children are `List (ListTree (ThreadId))`.\n\nWait, this is getting very confusing. Let me try to figure out how to approach this.\n\nAlternatively, perhaps the `ListTree` is not a standard data structure, but rather a local definition in the context. Let me check the definition of `ListTree` in the context.\n\nLooking at the context, `ListTree` is defined as:\n```tactics\nstructure ListTree {α : Sort u_1",
      "t₂ : ThreadId → (@Scope V)\n | valid, t₁, t₂ => match valid.scopes.meet t₁ t₂ with\n   | some scope => {threads := scope, valid := sorry}\n```\n\nThe error is in the line:\n```tactics\n⊢ scope ∈ Pop.ValidScopes.scopes valid\n```\nThe `sorry` tactic is used here, meaning the proof is incomplete.\n\nTo fix this error, we need to prove that `scope` (which is `[t₁, t₂]`) is an element of `valid.scopes`.\nLooking at the structure of `ListTree` and the membership operation, we need to show that `[t₁, t₂]` is in the `ListTree` `valid.scopes`.\n\nHowever, `valid` is an arbitrary `ValidScopes` and `t₁`, `t₂` are arbitrary `ThreadId`. There's no prior information guaranteeing that `[t₁, t₂]` is in `valid.scopes`.\n\nThis suggests a potential issue with the definition of `jointScope` or the assumptions under which it's defined. If `valid` is constructed such that its `scopes` doesn't contain `[t₁, t₂]`, the proof will fail.\n\nHowever, given the constraints, we need to complete the proof. The simplest way is to replace `sorry` with `simp`, hoping that `simp` can resolve the membership goal.\n\n```tactics\nimport Mathlib\n\nvariable [BEq]\n\nabbrev BlockingSemantics := List BlockingKinds\n\ndef BlockingKinds.toString : BlockingKinds → String\n  | .Read2ReadPred => \"R → R (P)\"\n  | .Read2ReadNoPred => \"R → R (NP)\"\n  | .Read2WritePred => \"R → W (P)\"\n  | .Read2WriteNoPred => \"R → W (NP)\"\n  | .Write2Read => \"W → R\"\n  | .Write2Write => \"W → W\"\n\ninstance : ToString BlockingKinds where toString := BlockingKinds.toString\n\nclass ArchReq where\n  (type : Type 0)\n  (instBEq : BEq type)\n  (instInhabited : Inhabited type)\n  (instToString : ToString type)\n  (prettyPrint : type → String := instToString.toString)\n  (isPermanentRead : type → Bool := λ _ => false)\n\nvariable [ArchReq]\n\ninductive Atomicity where\n  | nonatomic : Atomicity\n  | transactional : Atomicity\n  | atomic : Atomicity\n  deriving BEq, Inhabited\n\ninstance : ToString Atomicity where toString\n  | .nonatomic => \"\"\n  | .transactional => \"t\"\n  | .atomic => \"a\"\n\nstructure ReadRequest where\n addr : Address\n reads_from : Option RequestId\n atomicity : Atomicity\n val : Value\n deriving BEq, Inhabited\n\nstructure WriteRequest where\n addr : Address\n val : ConditionalValue\n atomicity : Atomicity\n deriving BEq, Inhabited\n\ninstance : BEq ArchReq.type := ArchReq.instBEq\ninstance : Inhabited ArchReq.type := ArchReq.instInhabited\ninstance : ToString ArchReq.type := ArchReq.instToString\n\ninductive BasicRequest\n | read : ReadRequest → ArchReq.type → BasicRequest\n | write : WriteRequest → ArchReq.type → BasicRequest\n | fence : ArchReq.type → BasicRequest\n deriving BEq\n\ninstance : Inhabited BasicRequest where default := BasicRequest.fence default\n\ndef BasicRequest.atomicity : BasicRequest → Atomicity\n  | .read rr _ => rr.atomicity\n  | .write wr _ => wr.atomicity\n  | .fence _ => .nonatomic\n\ndef BasicRequest.toString : BasicRequest → String\n  | BasicRequest.read  rr ty =>\n    let tyStr := match s!\"{ty}\" with | \"\" => \"\" | str => s!\". {str}\"\n    s!\"R{rr.atomicity}{tyStr} {rr.addr.prettyPrint}\" ++ match rr.val with | none => \"\" | some v => s!\" // {v}\"\n  | BasicRequest.write  wr ty =>\n    let tyStr := match s!\"{ty}\" with | \"\" => \"\" | str => s!\". {str}\"\n    s!\"W{wr.atomicity}{tyStr} {wr.addr.prettyPrint} {wr.val}\"\n  | BasicRequest.fence ty =>\n    let tyStr := match s!\"{ty}\" with | \"\" => \"\" | str => s!\". {str}\"\n    s!\"Fence{tyStr}\"\n\ndef BasicRequest.prettyPrint : BasicRequest → String\n  | BasicRequest.read rr ty =>\n    let valStr := match rr.val with\n      | none => \"\"\n      | some val => s!\"({val})\"\n    let tyStr := match s!\"{ArchReq.prettyPrint ty}\" with\n      | \"\" => \"\"\n      | str => s!\".{str}\"\n    s!\"R{rr.atomicity}{tyStr} {rr.addr.prettyPrint}{valStr}\"\n  | BasicRequest.write  wr ty =>\n    let tyStr := match s!\"{ty}\" with\n      | \"\" => \"\"\n      | str => s!\"